-- Russia to Prepare Hard-to-Recover Oil-Tax Incentives by Spring
-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v
-- 2012-12-18T19:01:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-18/russia-to-prepare-hard-to-recover-oil-tax-incentives-by-spring.html
Russia , the world’s biggest energy
exporter, will consider tax proposals to stimulate output of
hard-to-recover oil next spring, according to a document
 published  today.  Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev ordered the Finance Ministry
and “other interested government agencies” to prepare tax-code
amendments for submission to the Cabinet in February and to
lawmakers in March, according to a plan published on the
government’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Arkhipov in Moscow at 
 iarkhipov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  